    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Internet"><a href="#Internet" class="headerlink" title="Internet"></a>Internet</h1><h2 id="Media"><a href="#Media" class="headerlink" title="Media"></a>Media</h2><p>More and more people no longer read newspaper or watch TV programs to get news. They get news about the world through the internet. Is this a positive or negative development ?</p><h3 id="Mind-Mapping"><a href="#Mind-Mapping" class="headerlink" title="Mind Mapping"></a>Mind Mapping</h3><p><img src="/2022/06/30/writing-for-IELTS/Media.png" alt="Media"></p><h3 id="Words-or-Sentences"><a href="#Words-or-Sentences" class="headerlink" title="Words or Sentences"></a>Words or Sentences</h3><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">First:</span><br><span class="line">While I accept that surfing the internet to read news can sometimes have a positive effect on the user, I believe that it is more likely to have a harmful impact. </span><br><span class="line">Second:</span><br><span class="line">fragmented time //碎片化时间 like wolking time,have dinner in a restaurant and so on.</span><br><span class="line">The web is rich in resources, and you can search for more news you want to know. </span><br><span class="line">Internet does a great job in accelerating the circulation（加速传播） of the news.</span><br><span class="line">Third and fourth:</span><br><span class="line">Electrical newspapers make it a much more difficult thing to have deep reading and thorough thinking as they advocate fast and superficial reading with enormous information, while printed ones encourage slow and deep reading with proper amounts of exact information.</span><br><span class="line">To be specific, many pieces of news appearing on the Internet are inaccurate and unreliable, even the coverage towards the same event differs largely, which will consume readers or viewers a large amount of time and energy to ascertain the authenticity（确认真实性） of the news. By contrast, based on careful authorized steps and censorship（授权步骤和审查）, most of the resources from newspapers and TV programs are confirmed and dependable. Not to mention that traditional media can help people access the in-depth reports（深度报道）.</span><br><span class="line">Fifh:</span><br><span class="line">All in all, Internet has certainly revolutionised news propagation, but not all of the outcomes of this revolution have been positive.To some degree, getting news through printed newspapers or television are still irreplaceable.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h2 id="Security-and-Convenience"><a href="#Security-and-Convenience" class="headerlink" title="Security and Convenience"></a>Security and Convenience</h2><h3 id="Mind-Mapping-1"><a href="#Mind-Mapping-1" class="headerlink" title="Mind Mapping"></a>Mind Mapping</h3><p><img src="/2022/06/30/writing-for-IELTS/securityandconvenience.png" alt="securityandconvenience"></p><h3 id="Words-or-Sentences-1"><a href="#Words-or-Sentences-1" class="headerlink" title="Words or Sentences"></a>Words or Sentences</h3><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">First:</span><br><span class="line">Opinions on a digital society has been contradictory with severe tension and incompatibility between the concerns for data privacy and the pursuit of convenience.</span><br><span class="line">Second:</span><br><span class="line">vulnerability //弱点,攻击</span><br><span class="line">manipulate vt. 熟练操作</span><br><span class="line">hack into vi. 侵入（他人的计算机系统）</span><br><span class="line">vigilance n. 警惕（性）</span><br><span class="line">elaborate adj. 精心制作的</span><br><span class="line">fraud n. 诈骗</span><br><span class="line">Many argue that sensitive information registered online leads to the vulnerability of personal security and constant harassment. </span><br><span class="line">A minute after you browse certain applications, you get a call promoting their products immediately, and on a continuous basis. These side effects are eating up the benefits it can bring.</span><br><span class="line">Third and fourth:</span><br><span class="line">give up eating for fear of chocking.</span><br><span class="line">Simply a swipe on the phone allows us to pay without cash, to have the goods delivered to the door, and to keep in frequent contact with friends thousand miles away.</span><br><span class="line">Especially against the backdrop of the long-lasting pandemic, it is impossible to go anywhere without the green health code and travel records. </span><br><span class="line">Therefore, putting personal particulars online has become an irreversible trend, not only as the pathway towards personal convenience but also the necessity for social development.</span><br><span class="line">Fifh:</span><br><span class="line">In conclusion, I strongly believe that the advantages of storing personal information online have exceeded the risks and it complies with the requirement of social advancement.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h1 id="Education"><a href="#Education" class="headerlink" title="Education"></a>Education</h1><h2 id="Library"><a href="#Library" class="headerlink" title="Library"></a>Library</h2><p>Students can easily access information online, so libraries are no longer necessary. To what extent do you agree or disagree?</p><h3 id="Mind-Mapping-2"><a href="#Mind-Mapping-2" class="headerlink" title="Mind Mapping"></a>Mind Mapping</h3><p><img src="/2022/06/30/writing-for-IELTS/Library.png" alt="Library"></p><h3 id="Words-or-Sentences-2"><a href="#Words-or-Sentences-2" class="headerlink" title="Words or Sentences"></a>Words or Sentences</h3><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Second:</span><br><span class="line">There is no denying (不可否认的是) that the number of library users is declining, as most information searchers have turned to the Internet, the biggest source of information.</span><br><span class="line">people are able to learn all subjects and read various books with the click of a mouse，without the limitations of time and place.</span><br><span class="line">Third and fourth:</span><br><span class="line">quiet environment</span><br><span class="line">Despite the popularity of online reading these days, some people still prefer to read print books.The touch of paper gives them peace of mind,which can give them a different experience than reading on the electronic device.</span><br><span class="line">This offers us an opportunity to befriend with them just because of reading the same book like &quot;（书名）The Old Man and the Sea&quot;​</span><br><span class="line">socialise //社交</span><br><span class="line">interact with //互动</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
    
    
    
